Date:    Fri, 29 Jun 90 09:54:23 -0700
From:    EETP735@CALSTATE.BITNET
Subject: RE: Oversized mail.

regarding:

<I haven't narrowed it down to an exact combination of what must be
<replaced when this crash occurs. But replacing (not updating) the
<system, re-installing TOP and Microsoft mail, and deleting the
<start-up screen seem like the best solution we have right now.

at Cal State Chico, we have experienced some conflict between Microsoft
Mail and other inits, etc in the system folder.
If you can eliminate the problem by moving the startup screen,
the problem is probably a conflict between the startup screen loader
and some other init or system file.

Try taking the inits you have out of the system folder one at a time
and rebooting...this will help ypu narrow down the culprit.

Sometimes newer versions of inits solve conflict problems with
other popular DAs and inits.

Fran Holtsberry
Publications Editor
